* save/restore a reader (with relocation upon reloading)

* same for the Lightning-free case

* install a set of pre-compiled readers

* compatibility with Guile 1.[64]

* expose the standard reader specs to Scheme, impl. `scm_to_reader_spec ()'

* implement a case-insensitive token reader

* augment the reader library: R5RS, Guile, Guile + keywords, Skribe

* re-implement `read-enable' and `read-hash-extend' so that they modify
  a module-local reader (which may be lazily instantiated)

